---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';

const city = 'Jacksonville';
const slug = 'jacksonville';

const localBusinessSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "LocalBusiness",
  "@id": `https://hugheyllc.com/florida/${slug}/#business`,
  "name": "Hughey LLC — Law Firm Marketing Consultant",
  "description": `Independent law firm marketing consultant serving ${city}, Florida. Strategy, attribution, and agency accountability for law firms.`,
  "url": `https://hugheyllc.com/florida/${slug}/`,
  "telephone": "+17274833222",
  "email": "joe@joehughey.com",
  "image": "https://hugheyllc.com/hughey-logo.png",
  "priceRange": "$$",
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "addressLocality": city,
    "addressRegion": "FL",
    "addressCountry": "US"
  },
  "areaServed": [
    { "@type": "City", "name": city },
    { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Duval County, FL" },
    { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Clay County, FL" },
    { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "St. Johns County, FL" }
  ],
  "founder": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "Joe Hughey",
    "url": "https://hugheyllc.com/about/"
  },
  "sameAs": [
    "https://www.linkedin.com/in/joehughey/",
    "https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=61577138003264"
  ]
};

const breadcrumbSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://hugheyllc.com" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Florida", "item": "https://hugheyllc.com/florida/" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": city, "item": `https://hugheyllc.com/florida/${slug}/` }
  ]
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`Law Firm Marketing Consultant ${city}, FL | Hughey LLC`}
  description={`Independent law firm marketing consultant serving ${city}, Florida. Attribution, strategy, and agency accountability for North Florida law firms.`}
  canonical={`https://hugheyllc.com/florida/${slug}/`}
  schema={[localBusinessSchema, breadcrumbSchema]}
>
  <div style="background: var(--ink); color: var(--white); min-height: 100vh;">
    <PageHero
      eyebrow={`${city} • Duval County`}
      heading={`Law Firm Marketing Consultant<br /><em>${city}, FL</em>`}
      subheading={`Independent strategy and attribution for ${city} law firms. The largest legal market in North Florida — and one of the least competitive in the state per attorney.`}
    />

    <div style="padding: 72px 0;">
      <div class="w">
        <div class="city-grid">
          <div class="city-body">
            <p>Jacksonville is North Florida's largest legal market and the geographically largest city in the continental US. Duval County alone has more than 5,000 active attorneys, with additional density in Clay, Nassau, and St. Johns counties. The market is unusual for Florida: less saturated than Miami, Tampa, or Orlando — but with rapid population growth from Northeast and Midwest transplants reshaping which marketing channels actually produce retained clients.</p>

            <p>For Jacksonville law firms, the opportunity is real. The challenge is that most firms here haven't updated their marketing operation in a decade. <a href="/">Independent marketing strategy</a> for a Jacksonville firm usually starts with rebuilding the measurement layer from scratch.</p>

            <h2>The Jacksonville Legal Market</h2>

            <p>Personal injury is the most contested space, with national firms like Morgan & Morgan headquartered here and aggressive regional firms like Farah & Farah dominating local airtime, billboards, and Google Ads. Outside of PI, Jacksonville is a strong market for insurance defense (FCCI Group, Zurich, and major carriers have local operations), maritime and admiralty (Mayport Naval Station, Jacksonville Port, transportation logistics), and family law for the military population at NAS Jax and Kings Bay.</p>

            <p>Google Ads CPCs are meaningfully lower than Tampa or Orlando — "Jacksonville car accident lawyer" generally runs $50–$90, less than half of South Florida — but Local Services Ads have become the bigger story. LSA leads in Duval County frequently outperform PPC on cost per retained client, but most firms don't measure the two channels separately and end up over-investing in the wrong one.</p>

            <h2>Why {city} Law Firms Work With Me</h2>

            <p>Most Jacksonville firms I work with are spending $8,000–$50,000 per month on marketing — less than their South Florida counterparts but still enough that measurement matters. Common situations I see:</p>

            <ul>
              <li><strong>Military and base-population intake</strong> — firms serving NAS Jax, Kings Bay, and Mayport personnel need different intake handling (deployment timelines, JAG referrals, PCS moves) than civilian clients</li>
              <li><strong>I-95 and I-10 corridor PI cases</strong> — Jacksonville sits on two of Florida's busiest interstate corridors; PI firms routinely fail to track out-of-state crash victim leads separately from local Duval traffic</li>
              <li><strong>St. Johns County transplant boom</strong> — explosive growth in St. Augustine, Nocatee, and Ponte Vedra means estate planning, real estate, and family law leads from these zip codes have different lifetime value than urban Duval intake</li>
              <li><strong>National firm competition on local terms</strong> — Morgan & Morgan and similar firms outspend local firms on broad PI keywords, so local firms need a long-tail and GBP strategy that doesn't try to compete head-to-head</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>What the Engagement Looks Like</h2>

            <p>A Jacksonville engagement typically starts with a 30-day analytics and intake audit: connecting your GA4, CallRail or CallTrackingMetrics, CRM (Lawmatics, Clio Grow, or PracticePanther), and ad platforms. Most Jacksonville firms find their first surprise within two weeks — usually that Local Services Ads or referrals are outperforming everything else, but they've been over-funding paid search out of habit.</p>

            <p>From there it's strategic work: agency accountability, intake process redesign, GBP optimization, and a 12-month plan. I'm based in St. Petersburg; Jacksonville engagements are conducted remotely with quarterly on-site visits.</p>
          </div>

          <aside class="city-side">
            <div class="side-card">
              <h3>Service Area</h3>
              <p>Jacksonville • Jacksonville Beach • Ponte Vedra • St. Augustine • Orange Park • Fernandina Beach • Duval, Clay, Nassau, and St. Johns counties</p>
            </div>
            <div class="side-card">
              <h3>Common Practice Areas</h3>
              <p>Personal Injury • Insurance Defense • Maritime Law • Military Family Law • Estate Planning • Real Estate • Business Litigation</p>
            </div>
            <div class="side-card cta-card">
              <h3>Talk to Joe</h3>
              <p>Direct conversation about your firm's numbers. No sales pitch.</p>
              <a href="/contact/" class="cta-btn">Schedule a Free Call →</a>
            </div>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="padding: 64px 0; background: rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.05); border-top: 1px solid rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.15);">
      <div class="w">
        <div style="max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; text-align: center;">
          <h2 style="font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 40px); font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 16px;">Ready to See Your Real Numbers?</h2>
          <p style="font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72); margin-bottom: 32px;">If your Jacksonville firm is spending serious money on marketing and can't tell which channel is producing retained clients, that's the conversation worth having.</p>
          <a href="/contact/" style="display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 9px; background: var(--gold); color: var(--ink); font-family: var(--man); font-weight: 800; font-size: 13px; letter-spacing: 0.07em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 18px 36px; border-radius: 2px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.25s; box-shadow: 0 4px 28px rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.42);">
            Schedule a Free Call →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    em { color: var(--glt); font-style: italic; }
    .city-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) 320px;
      gap: 60px;
      align-items: start;
      max-width: 1180px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
    .city-body { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.85; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.82); }
    .city-body p { margin-bottom: 24px; }
    .city-body h2 {
      font-size: clamp(24px, 3vw, 32px);
      font-weight: 800;
      color: var(--white);
      margin: 48px 0 20px;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }
    .city-body ul {
      margin: 0 0 24px;
      padding-left: 22px;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 10px;
    }
    .city-body li { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78); }
    .city-body a {
      color: var(--glt);
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 3px;
    }
    .city-body a:hover { color: var(--white); }
    .city-body strong { color: var(--white); font-weight: 700; }
    .city-side {
      position: sticky;
      top: 140px;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 18px;
    }
    .side-card {
      background: rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.05);
      border: 1px solid rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.18);
      border-radius: 4px;
      padding: 22px;
    }
    .side-card h3 {
      font-size: 12px;
      font-weight: 700;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      color: var(--glt);
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .side-card p {
      font-size: 14px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72);
      margin: 0;
    }
    .cta-card { background: rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.1); }
    .cta-btn {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 6px;
      margin-top: 14px;
      background: var(--gold);
      color: var(--ink);
      font-family: var(--man);
      font-weight: 800;
      font-size: 12px;
      letter-spacing: 0.07em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      padding: 12px 22px;
      border-radius: 2px;
      text-decoration: none;
      transition: background 0.2s;
    }
    .cta-btn:hover { background: var(--glt); }
    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .city-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .city-side { position: static; }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
